1
00:00:02,340 --> 00:00:04,870
Last Episode

2
00:00:05,940 --> 00:00:09,640
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

3
00:00:14,990 --> 00:00:17,530
You're working very late.

4
00:00:17,530 --> 00:00:19,660
Yes, because there's a lot of work to do.

5
00:00:19,660 --> 00:00:22,020
- Please continue with your work.
- Yes.

6
00:00:26,710 --> 00:00:29,260
B: Placing sales focus on young adults, target strategy failed
Need to modify to a more designed side

7
00:00:29,260 --> 00:00:30,790
C: Popularity for  both men and woman

8
00:00:30,790 --> 00:00:33,080
Sales are good, thus target market is restricted and extended to the 20's to 30's

9
00:00:39,980 --> 00:00:42,120
Okay.

10
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:02,120
I'm totally exhausted today.

11
00:01:02,930 --> 00:01:05,450
I'll see you tomorrow, Won.

12
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:21,530
Stop clinging onto me.

13
00:01:21,530 --> 00:01:24,930
I don't want to. There's so much work to do that I'm tired.

14
00:01:24,930 --> 00:01:27,600
For whose benefit are you working that hard? Workaholic.

15
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:33,210
That's right. Please cheer the tired me.

16
00:01:34,090 --> 00:01:39,240
I understand, but if we fall going up like this, we both will be hurt.

17
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:44,380
Then let's get hurt. We'll get hurt, go to the hospital and lie in bed together.

18
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:55,320
Are you going to keep making it impossible for me to live?

19
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:58,200
You're threatening me right now, right?

20
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:00,250
Don't regret it.

21
00:02:02,550 --> 00:02:04,500
Then, I'm also going to make it hard for you.

22
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:06,080
Hey!

23
00:02:08,660 --> 00:02:10,450
What are you guys doing?

24
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:13,910
Unni.

25
00:02:13,910 --> 00:02:16,330
Aren't you guys being a bit too ardent?

26
00:02:16,330 --> 00:02:17,840
Madam Choi, that's not it...

27
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:21,340
A shock is about to come over me. Should I go back out?

28
00:02:21,340 --> 00:02:22,880
Oh, no. Come in.

29
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:28,670
No, no. I don't think it's good for the baby. Continue with what you're doing.

30
00:02:28,670 --> 00:02:31,800
Unni! What are we going to do?

31
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:36,080
What? Let's just continue what we were doing.

32
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:38,850
Hey! How am I going to look at Unni's face again?

33
00:02:38,850 --> 00:02:42,150
She is going to think that I was here all this time when she wasn't.

34
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:43,690
But that's correct.

35
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:46,350
Hey!

36
00:02:49,890 --> 00:02:52,070
Hey.

37
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:34,240
If one is pregnant, she usually changes her taste in food and her appetite becomes bigger.

38
00:03:35,370 --> 00:03:38,880
Then you should eat good food. What's with the boiled eggs?

39
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:43,100
Be warned. From now on, I'm going to tell you everything I want to eat.

40
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:47,640
I will get it even if I have to search all over the country, so you just have to tell me.

41
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:53,260
But, the house we'll live together in...

42
00:03:53,260 --> 00:03:56,990
I think we have to look for it as soon as possible. I feel awkward with Won now.

43
00:03:56,990 --> 00:03:57,890
Huh?

44
00:03:57,890 --> 00:04:02,900
No, when I got home after my last flight and prepared for a few days' vacation,

45
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:05,490
the two of them are stuck together.

46
00:04:05,490 --> 00:04:08,730
That's why I just left the house.

47
00:04:08,730 --> 00:04:11,680
Then, let's just go to my house.

48
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:17,020
I knew you'd say that, so I reserved a moving van in advance.

49
00:04:17,020 --> 00:04:19,320
Please move my stuff today.

50
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:20,990
A moving van?

51
00:04:20,990 --> 00:04:26,250
I can't sleep if my sleeping place changes, so you can't leave anything out.

52
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:28,940
As expected, you are a meticulous woman.

53
00:04:39,910 --> 00:04:43,270
Isn't this you guys' 1+1 story?

54
00:04:52,420 --> 00:04:53,960
What is this?

55
00:04:57,290 --> 00:05:00,480
I will Never Love You
Chapter 1

56
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,240
What... what is this?

57
00:05:25,890 --> 00:05:28,660
I Will Never Love You
Writer and Artist: Oh Dae Bok

58
00:05:30,220 --> 00:05:32,280
You! Oh Dae Bok!

59
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:34,650
Oh, Noona! You were home?

60
00:05:35,430 --> 00:05:38,630
You... the script on my desk!

61
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:39,860
Script?

62
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:42,600
Tell me everything honestly now!

63
00:05:44,230 --> 00:05:45,830
Noona, the audience really loves it!

64
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:50,200
Who told you you can use someone else's story without even asking for permission?

65
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:55,360
The people really like you and Hyung Won! There is a really good response from the people around me!

66
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:59,380
Hey! You should have told me in advance! So rude!

67
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:02,440
Noona, for your younger brother, can't you just close your eyes to this?

68
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:06,140
For the first time, I got recognized for what I've been wanting to do!

69
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:11,640
What?

70
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:21,710
Aww, what in the world! My son has this kind of skill! Thank you!

71
00:06:21,710 --> 00:06:25,870
So  this is what you've been doing when you locked yourself in your room?

72
00:06:25,870 --> 00:06:29,370
Yes. I really worked hard on it.

73
00:06:29,370 --> 00:06:32,520
What are you going to do? Have you told Won?

74
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:35,100
No. But I will.

75
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:37,850
I also didn't know it would be received with a good response.

76
00:06:37,850 --> 00:06:42,870
Son, don't get too blown away by things like this,

77
00:06:44,220 --> 00:06:46,760
and just study as usual.

78
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:51,420
So this guy is Won, and the girl is Ha Na?

79
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:52,580
Yes, that's correct.

80
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:56,070
It's the first time an opportunity came to me. Help me out.

81
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:58,260
I'll see you later.

82
00:07:11,930 --> 00:07:13,300
I Will Never Love You

83
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,570
Chapter 1
Writer/Artist: Oh Dae Bok

84
00:07:14,570 --> 00:07:19,780
Wow. It's not the drawing skill he had back with Jajjang Man.

85
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:22,030
He did draw very well, didn't he?

86
00:07:22,030 --> 00:07:25,480
I thought he gave up on drawing, but I guess not.

87
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:28,420
He's the same as I, not giving up so easily.

88
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:30,650
I'll give you that.

89
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:32,620
Don't forget our dinner.

90
00:07:32,620 --> 00:07:36,160
Ah, right! I forgot about it!

91
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:39,450
Tomorrow will be the announcement of the project results, so depending on the outcome,

92
00:07:39,450 --> 00:07:42,790
I might have an appointment.

93
00:07:42,790 --> 00:07:46,450
You are slowly putting your work first, before me.

94
00:07:46,450 --> 00:07:48,700
I'm giving you a warning, Oh Ha Na.

95
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:50,590
What did I do?

96
00:07:50,590 --> 00:07:53,980
Being a workaholic is a type of disease.

97
00:07:53,980 --> 00:07:57,860
What? Disease! Hey!

98
00:07:58,910 --> 00:08:02,400
Come out. I couldn't say what I wanted to say last night.

99
00:08:08,210 --> 00:08:11,790
Does working overtime and attending work dinners constitute being a workaholic? Is it a disease?

100
00:08:11,790 --> 00:08:14,520
Yes! That's why when you're with me, you grumble about being tired.

101
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:16,570
Have you spent time with me outside these days?

102
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:19,230
Can you not understand that much for the sake of your working girlfriend?

103
00:08:19,230 --> 00:08:21,950
I'm telling you to do it moderately! Just put everything down.

104
00:08:21,950 --> 00:08:24,880
The problem right now is that you're trying to do everything!

105
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,830
Problem? Did you just say, problem?

106
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:30,270
Hey, that's just saying I am responsible for things!

107
00:08:30,270 --> 00:08:33,790
For someone who's responsible, you change your dates with me at your whim.

108
00:08:33,790 --> 00:08:36,070
What's your priority, exactly?

109
00:08:36,070 --> 00:08:38,930
I did not do anything for me to hear that from you!

110
00:08:38,930 --> 00:08:40,890
No matter how busy I am, I spend weekends with you―

111
00:08:40,890 --> 00:08:44,090
What's the use of being together on weekends? You're always on the phone and looking at documents!

112
00:08:44,090 --> 00:08:47,810
You said you like the sight of me working! I didn't know you hate it!

113
00:08:47,810 --> 00:08:51,860
Since I know that now, I will never show you the side of me working!

114
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:10,130
For the contest exhibit for Tandy's new line,

115
00:09:10,130 --> 00:09:13,560
Assistant Hong from the Marketing Team and Min Ji from the Design Team...

116
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:16,890
Both of your work has passed

117
00:09:20,860 --> 00:09:25,970
Team Leader Oh's idea also reached the final round, but if we only reinforce our marketing strategy,

118
00:09:25,970 --> 00:09:30,080
we decided that the proposals of the two have bigger feasibility.

119
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:35,780
Team Leaders, you must work harder.

120
00:09:35,780 --> 00:09:40,410
Isn't it that the capabilities of the team flourish under the team leader's efforts?

121
00:09:40,410 --> 00:09:42,720
Isn't that right, Team Leader Oh?

122
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:49,100
You will create a national shoe.

123
00:09:49,850 --> 00:09:51,180
The idea sound good!

124
00:09:51,180 --> 00:09:52,820
Really?

125
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:56,250
We thought it would be nice to create shoes that can be worn for all four seasons,

126
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:59,080
we created the idea of using fabric and natural materials.

127
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:03,310
If it succeeds, it will be a successful item that can be launched regardless of the season.

128
00:10:03,310 --> 00:10:07,480
Alright. I understand. I'll review it more.

129
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,240
Yes.

130
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:21,040
It must have been an odd feeling, Oh Ha Na.

131
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:25,200
Seeing your hoobaes shine brightly... If you acknowledge their work, you must also feel like you're being pushed aside.

132
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:28,220
But if you don't, it also hurts your pride.

133
00:10:28,220 --> 00:10:30,240
Am I too childish?

134
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:30,900
Hey.

135
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:33,540
Hey! That's just natural. Be strong!

136
00:10:33,540 --> 00:10:35,240
Thanks.

137
00:10:45,340 --> 00:10:48,010
What's with your expression? Did you fight?

138
00:10:48,010 --> 00:10:51,730
I'm worried that we'll just grow old arguing.

139
00:10:51,730 --> 00:10:56,690
Eh, no way. You even went all the way to Paris for love.

140
00:10:56,690 --> 00:11:01,660
It's not about the big ones. We keep fighting about minor things.

141
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:04,950
There are things now that I can't just let go.

142
00:11:04,950 --> 00:11:10,220
That's what you call the 'fight for dominance' between lovers. A war of nerves.

143
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:11,720
A war of nerves?

144
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:13,910
Yes. You should endure well at this time.

145
00:11:13,910 --> 00:11:18,680
You should not let her win so easily.

146
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:42,990
I'm jealous.  I'd like to love and fight too.

147
00:11:42,990 --> 00:11:47,540
Oh right, someone told me to give you this.

148
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:49,170
For me?

149
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:56,020
Keep up your strength, Sunbaenim.

150
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:58,240
From Dong Geon.

151
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:02,250
Are you making fun of your superior right now?

152
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:08,070
Why? This is also one form of love. Between colleagues.

153
00:12:12,370 --> 00:12:16,440
Between colleagues? Then you put your two fingers together.

154
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:19,840
I'm really lonely.

155
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:29,120
You shouldn't be working too hard.

156
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:32,140
You must be into your work too much.

157
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:33,140
Are you getting off work?

158
00:12:33,140 --> 00:12:37,020
I'm at the age where I have to take care of my health even if I'm doing my best for it.

159
00:12:37,020 --> 00:12:38,750
I'll leave first.

160
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,510
Okay.

161
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,940
I should rest too.

162
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:54,410
Team Leader Oh.

163
00:12:54,410 --> 00:12:57,160
Oh, you came to pick up Min Ji?

164
00:12:57,160 --> 00:13:01,800
Yes.  Min Ji really likes working with you.

165
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:06,030
- Really?
- This morning, she went to work filled with enthusiasm.

166
00:13:06,030 --> 00:13:11,920
She likes working with you, but she said you're like a wall that she can't climb over.

167
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:13,980
Really?

168
00:13:13,980 --> 00:13:17,150
Team Leader, we'll leave first.

169
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:18,690
Work hard.

170
00:13:20,190 --> 00:13:22,000
Careful.

171
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,940
I'm okay.

172
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:47,690
Did my mom get a lot better?

173
00:13:50,170 --> 00:13:54,760
I just got back home from a flight, so it's only now that I got your package. I'll check it right away.

174
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:59,610
Okay. I'll leave my mom in your care.

175
00:13:59,610 --> 00:14:01,920
I'll visit you later.

176
00:14:08,660 --> 00:14:15,680
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

177
00:14:34,230 --> 00:14:37,570
This looks like formal dress for when you and Ha Na get married.

178
00:14:37,570 --> 00:14:42,590
I know.  I don't know how she knew my size or Ha Na's size.

179
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:45,340
There's no way she wouldn't know that.

180
00:14:45,340 --> 00:14:49,850
Women can know another woman's size just by looking.

181
00:14:49,850 --> 00:14:52,820
Speaking of her, did she regain consciousness?

182
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:57,540
Yes. They say she's regained consciousness, and is even eating now.

183
00:14:57,540 --> 00:14:59,460
That's good.

184
00:15:02,390 --> 00:15:06,840
I... am going to live with Jong Hoon.

185
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:07,740
What?

186
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:10,810
I'll give birth to my child and live with him.

187
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:12,460
Then we'll get married.

188
00:15:12,460 --> 00:15:15,470
Isn't that being too progressive?

189
00:15:15,470 --> 00:15:20,460
Since I'm old now, I got to know how tremendous the word 'constant' is.

190
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:24,090
Before I change my mind, I will live with him, and then marriage can come next.

191
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:26,270
Ohh, Madam Choi.

192
00:15:26,270 --> 00:15:30,760
You got me again. You're amazing.

193
00:15:45,940 --> 00:15:49,660
Is he back from his flight or what?

194
00:15:49,660 --> 00:15:51,980
Why hasn't he contacted me?

195
00:15:57,580 --> 00:15:59,860
I sweat when eating grilled samgyupsal.

196
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:02,450
I also sweat when I eat ramen noodles.

197
00:16:02,450 --> 00:16:05,870
I sweat when I get back from my sixth plate in a buffet.

198
00:16:05,870 --> 00:16:08,000
I sweat this much,

199
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,660
but I don't know why I don't lose weight.

200
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:15,650
When I was young—

201
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:21,250
If you got back from your flight, why didn't you contact me?

202
00:16:21,250 --> 00:16:24,270
Oh, I just had some stuff to do.

203
00:16:31,330 --> 00:16:35,430
After what you said, I took some time to think.

204
00:16:37,150 --> 00:16:41,110
These days, I've been working non-stop.

205
00:16:41,110 --> 00:16:43,770
Did you realize that just now?

206
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:47,190
My hoobaes thought of the ideas I couldn't think of even already went crazy thinking about it.

207
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:49,900
I have things I want to be recognized for.

208
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:54,390
Thanks to that, I am becoming less the focus of your interest.

209
00:16:54,390 --> 00:16:57,260
No, it's not like that.

210
00:16:57,260 --> 00:16:59,750
It's not.

211
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:02,090
Just...

212
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:06,900
Just don't forget there are things more important than work.

213
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:33,340
If it was something for your sake, if it's something you need,

214
00:17:33,340 --> 00:17:35,050
I'm approving no matter what.

215
00:17:35,050 --> 00:17:39,520
Never forget a thing, and remember all.

216
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:50,780
Get up, Choi Won.  Eat.  Eat.

217
00:17:50,780 --> 00:17:56,630
I'll be by your side.  I'll never leave you alone.

218
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,700
After saying all that.

219
00:18:05,790 --> 00:18:07,360
Oh, what?

220
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:09,400
Look over here.

221
00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:12,850
Where?

222
00:18:12,850 --> 00:18:17,220
Open the window and look over here.

223
00:18:27,710 --> 00:18:28,830
What is it?

224
00:18:28,830 --> 00:18:31,790
It's been a while since I've seen you here.

225
00:18:31,790 --> 00:18:33,410
That's true.

226
00:18:34,370 --> 00:18:36,660
I can see your angry expression.

227
00:18:36,660 --> 00:18:39,430
I can see all your expressions.

228
00:18:39,430 --> 00:18:44,350
Even when we're this far, we can see each other's expressions,

229
00:18:44,350 --> 00:18:47,650
cry together, be sad.

230
00:18:47,650 --> 00:18:52,530
We call each other to eat late-night snacks together if there's something that upsets me.

231
00:18:52,530 --> 00:18:54,870
You're feeling sorry, huh?

232
00:18:54,900 --> 00:19:00,700
Now, tell me, "I'll do anything you want until you're not mad."

233
00:19:02,690 --> 00:19:05,400
Apologize first.

234
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:08,140
I was wrong.

235
00:19:08,140 --> 00:19:11,520
And say the words I want to hear the most.

236
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:19,200
My number one priority, before work, is Choi Won.

237
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,970
Is your anger gone?

238
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,000
A little.

239
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,840
Hello.

240
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,700
Do you want to drink this?

241
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:57,960
This is refreshing, drink this.

242
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:00,810
Okay, thank you.

243
00:20:00,810 --> 00:20:08,880
Umm, So Eun. If you have time on the weekend, do you want to go see a movie?

244
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:11,640
I got some tickets but I have no one to go with...

245
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:13,230
I want to go too.

246
00:20:13,230 --> 00:20:15,710
I want to go together too.

247
00:20:15,710 --> 00:20:18,120
The three of you can go.

248
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,500
So Eun.

249
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:26,900
Sunday, 3 pm.  Tae Neung Theater. If you have time, come.

250
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:29,030
I'll wait.

251
00:20:29,030 --> 00:20:31,190
Please don't wait.

252
