665
00:53:39,670 --> 00:53:40,760
Really?

666
00:53:40,760 --> 00:53:42,480
Yes.

667
00:53:42,480 --> 00:53:44,640
Really?

668
00:53:45,680 --> 00:53:49,600
Then, am I becoming a grandmother?

669
00:53:51,490 --> 00:53:56,570
Before I have a child, I wanted to express my thanks to you.

670
00:53:58,000 --> 00:54:04,060
Hey. How can you say that? It's like I did not give birth to you.

671
00:54:04,060 --> 00:54:06,450
Along those lines,

672
00:54:08,770 --> 00:54:10,550
give me your hand.

673
00:54:16,290 --> 00:54:20,720
Thanks for marrying and living with me.

674
00:54:20,720 --> 00:54:22,860
It's good if I do it like that, right?

675
00:54:25,400 --> 00:54:27,890
Dad!

676
00:54:30,290 --> 00:54:31,670
You're cool!

677
00:54:32,200 --> 00:54:37,800
Please proceed with the Season 2 project with the two of you in charge.

678
00:54:38,400 --> 00:54:42,800
It started from your idea, and I believe you two have enough capacity to take it on.

679
00:54:42,810 --> 00:54:44,990
Is there any reason?

680
00:54:44,990 --> 00:54:48,020
Did we make you upset?

681
00:54:50,000 --> 00:54:53,200
I'm going to have a baby.

682
00:54:54,300 --> 00:54:58,000
- Really? Congratulations.
- From me too.

683
00:54:58,050 --> 00:54:59,350
Do you feel okay?

684
00:54:59,350 --> 00:55:03,020
Yeah, I'm okay. I want to be careful.

685
00:55:03,020 --> 00:55:07,960
Min Ji and Eun Jung, do whatever you want with this project.

686
00:55:07,960 --> 00:55:11,050
I will strongly support you from behind.

687
00:55:11,050 --> 00:55:14,110
But you were the one who set this all up.

688
00:55:14,110 --> 00:55:19,330
There's no need to be sorry. I'm going to do my best for my new life.

689
00:55:19,330 --> 00:55:22,370
You know, right? Whenever I start on something, I do it properly.

690
00:55:23,500 --> 00:55:28,560
I'm telling you  from this moment to do your very best in your respective roles.

691
00:55:28,600 --> 00:55:30,300
Yes.

692
00:55:32,610 --> 00:55:33,870
Here.

693
00:55:56,800 --> 00:55:59,560
I'm too late. I guess we won't be able to watch the movie.

694
00:55:59,600 --> 00:56:03,500
No, no. It's alright. You're very pretty today.

695
00:56:05,160 --> 00:56:07,640
What's the next course?

696
00:56:07,640 --> 00:56:08,870
What do you want to do?

697
00:56:08,870 --> 00:56:13,230
Did you ask me out on a date without any plans?

698
00:56:14,520 --> 00:56:16,240
- Uhh...
- I'm disappointed.

699
00:56:16,240 --> 00:56:20,210
That's not it. Right now, we were originally supposed to watch the movie.

700
00:56:20,240 --> 00:56:22,820
Should I go look for another movie?

701
00:56:22,840 --> 00:56:26,570
Follow me. I'll take you to a nice place today.

702
00:56:26,600 --> 00:56:30,800
Alright. Let's do whatever you want today. Let me carry your bag.

703
00:56:53,410 --> 00:56:56,990
Cha Seo Hoo Special Recital

704
00:57:10,370 --> 00:57:13,970
Excuse me. Here are flowers for you.

705
00:57:21,680 --> 00:57:24,280
I'm looking forward to a masterwork. - Oh Ha Na

706
00:57:27,270 --> 00:57:29,830
I must do especially well for today's performance.

707
00:57:29,870 --> 00:57:32,510
Mr. Cha's performance is always the best.

708
00:57:32,560 --> 00:57:34,240
How's your condition today?

709
00:57:34,240 --> 00:57:36,910
Yes. I'm at my best.

710
00:57:36,910 --> 00:57:40,280
There are a lot of important people who came today.

711
00:57:41,050 --> 00:57:42,580
Really?

712
00:57:48,560 --> 00:57:50,260
Let's go.

713
00:58:02,800 --> 00:58:06,700
I'm sorry I couldn't come last night. How would I know it would end late?

714
00:58:06,750 --> 00:58:09,890
But you never said anything. You made me feel awkward.

715
00:58:09,900 --> 00:58:12,260
You should say something, at least!

716
00:58:12,260 --> 00:58:14,640
If you couldn't make it, you should have called. Why is your phone turned off?

717
00:58:14,640 --> 00:58:16,860
I didn't know it was turned off.

718
00:58:18,360 --> 00:58:20,240
Do you think I'm acting like this because of last night?

719
00:58:20,240 --> 00:58:24,280
Oh yeah? Let's hear you out, and see how much you've been putting up with.

720
00:58:24,320 --> 00:58:28,260
Not properly cleaning last week, and touching my things without my permission and not even putting them back in place!

721
00:58:28,260 --> 00:58:31,450
Ignoring things you should be mindful of! Should I say more!

722
00:58:31,500 --> 00:58:35,700
Oh, really? Should I say mine now? Not giving me time for myself!

723
00:58:35,700 --> 00:58:40,900
Putting one of your socks everywhere and now they're all unpaired! Not cleaning the washroom after using it!

724
00:58:40,940 --> 00:58:43,550
More! Say more!

725
00:58:45,700 --> 00:58:48,400
Forget it. Let's stop it. There's no end to this.

726
00:58:48,400 --> 00:58:51,010
You knew me for the longest time, but you still don't know me?

727
00:58:51,040 --> 00:58:54,030
That's right! There's a lot I don't know about you as the days pass by.

728
00:58:54,600 --> 00:58:59,600
Hey, Oh Ha Na! Won't you come here! Finish talking before you go!

729
00:59:21,780 --> 00:59:23,210
Be careful.

730
00:59:28,090 --> 00:59:29,790
We'll be leaving.

731
00:59:29,800 --> 00:59:33,200
Bye. Let's go.

732
00:59:38,910 --> 00:59:40,660
Be careful.

733
00:59:40,690 --> 00:59:42,070
Why did you come for me?

734
00:59:42,070 --> 00:59:43,330
Sorry.

735
00:59:48,290 --> 00:59:51,230
You're preparing tonight's dinner, alright?

736
00:59:51,980 --> 00:59:54,860
What are you talking about? I bought dinner last night.

737
00:59:54,860 --> 00:59:56,480
It's your turn now.

738
00:59:56,480 --> 01:00:01,120
Where did you put the other half of your socks? They're all unpaired!

739
01:00:01,140 --> 01:00:03,160
I certainly put them in.

740
01:00:03,190 --> 01:00:06,410
Ah, right. You washed my shirt for tomorrow's flight, right?

741
01:00:06,410 --> 01:00:08,750
Ah! I forgot!

742
01:00:08,770 --> 01:00:11,760
What the heck? I have no clothes to wear tomorrow.

743
01:00:11,760 --> 01:00:15,890
Let's hurry. So tonight's dinner is on you, okay?

744
01:00:17,400 --> 01:00:21,050
Also, I registered for couple's yoga.

745
01:00:21,060 --> 01:00:22,960
Why? Why that?

746
01:00:23,010 --> 01:00:25,300
I heard it's good for natural birth.

747
01:00:25,320 --> 01:00:29,080
It regulates your breathing, and it helps in opening up. And when contraction starts, your breathing...

748
01:00:29,080 --> 01:00:30,980
I don't like those things.

749
01:00:30,980 --> 01:00:32,610
Why? Let's do it together.

750
01:00:32,640 --> 01:00:38,090
I will film our child's delivery, from start to finish.

751
01:00:38,090 --> 01:00:42,220
Don't do that. I don't like it. I don't like things like that.

752
01:00:42,220 --> 01:00:43,890
Also...

753
01:00:43,900 --> 01:00:45,700
- There's more?
- Of course.

754
01:00:46,500 --> 01:00:48,400
I already have it planned out.

755
01:00:48,400 --> 01:00:49,630
- Really?
- Yeah.

756
01:00:50,900 --> 01:00:53,500
- Let's eat out tonight.
- Okay!

757
01:00:54,910 --> 01:00:59,090
From being eternal long-time friends to being a married couple,

758
01:00:59,100 --> 01:01:03,600
we fought and made up countless times. We hated each other,

759
01:01:03,640 --> 01:01:06,680
and then we loved each other. And the cycle repeats over and over again.

760
01:01:16,000 --> 01:01:17,280
Wait, wait!

761
01:01:17,320 --> 01:01:20,180
You must give as much love as you receive.

762
01:01:20,200 --> 01:01:26,200
We personally learned and put that into action so that we can maintain the size of our love.

763
